timeline.bodyText:
usually, add/subtract methods that return an instance don't modify the existing instance because you can end up with confusing code like this:
Date today = new Date();
Timespan oneDay = ...;
Date tomorrow = today.add(oneDay);
System.out.println(tomorrow == today); // confusingly, prints true

